{
  "local_port": 55950,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm hungry what should I do?",
  "response": "When you're hungry, here's a structured approach to decide what to eat:\n\n1. **Assess Hunger Level**: \n   - **Starving?** Opt for something filling like a protein-rich meal (eggs, chicken, beans) with complex carbs (rice, whole-grain bread).\n   - **Just Snackish?** Grab a light snack (fruit, nuts, yogurt).\n\n2. **Check Available Ingredients**:\n   - **Leftovers**: Reheat pasta, rice, or soup.\n   - **Quick Meals**: Eggs (omelette, scrambled), sandwiches (PB&J, tuna, grilled cheese), wraps, or avocado toast.\n   - **Pantry Staples**: Canned beans, instant noodles, oatmeal, or cereal.\n\n3. **Time & Effort**:\n   - **Quick Fix**: Smoothie, yogurt bowl, or a piece of fruit with nut butter.\n   - **10-15 Minutes**: Stir-fry veggies with protein, scrambled eggs, or a baked potato.\n   - **More Time**: Cook a fresh meal like a hearty salad, stir-fry, or pasta dish.\n\n4. **Health & Dietary Needs**:\n   - **Healthy Options**: Salad with protein, steamed veggies, or a fruit/nut mix.\n   - **Comfort Food**: Grilled cheese, instant noodles, or pancakes.\n\n5. **Hydration Check**: Drink water first\u2014thirst can mimic hunger.\n\n6. **Last Resorts**:\n   - **Snacks**: Nuts, crackers, dark chocolate, or popcorn.\n   - **Takeout**: Order delivery if cooking isn\u2019t feasible.\n\n**Example Meals**:\n- **Omelette** with spinach and cheese.\n- **Avocado Toast** with a fried egg.\n- **Stir-Fry** with leftover rice, veggies, and soy sauce.\n- **Greek Yogurt** with honey and granola.\n\nChoose based on your cravings, time, and ingredients! \ud83c\udf74",
